V N K  -  P O X I S  M E S S A G E  Q U E U E  E X A M P L E

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A U T H O R:

Loi Huynh

DESCRIPTION:

This is an example about Linux Posix Message Queue. It is more than an example,
this also contains use-cases of Poxis Message Queue and also some its notice.

BINARY NAME:

[vnkmq]

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

USING:

#>:$ cd VNK_TemplateModule/build
#>:$ VNK_MBuild.bash -g        # To generate Makefile via CMAKE
#>:$ VNK_MBuild.bash -m        # To call "make"
#>:$ VNK_MBuild.bash -h        # To show build help
#>:$ ./vnkmq <arguments>       # To run built binary

TIPS:

- Call "VNK_MBuild.bash -g -m" to generate Makefile and doing "make" in a time.

NOTICE:

- You can need to build libs firstly.
- Example: to build libVNK_LibNotify_static.a, navigate to
  VNK_Library/VNK_LibNotify/build and call "VNK_MBuild.bash -g -m".

- The Posix Message Queue is NOT enabled in Windown Linux Sub-system.

OTHERS:

- Build script name: VNK_MBuild.bash.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
